</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ujontann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jontann</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/27/00 1:06:33 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.europa.com/~jmb/images/JonIcon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Wurmslayer Overrated?</span><hr size=1> Ok, I've been meaning to post about this for a while, but I just haven't gotten around to it.  I really don't see what the big whoop is about Wurmslayer.  Given, it has some stat buffs and a nice high damage rating, but it's <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> SLOW</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  Considering what a pain in the ass the quest is to finish up, could someone enlighten me as to how this weapon is actually worth the trouble of getting?  I see <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> so</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> many people working to chase down the quest NPC to get it that to me it's almost sad considering it's really, IMHO at least, a sub-standard weapon compared to what else is available to folks high level enough to complete the quest (Fayguard Parrying Dagger, Jade Mace, Lamentation, etc.)  <br>
<br>
At least for tanks who are more interested in taunting and taking hits rather than dealing damage, it seems to me that you'd be much better off with a faster weapon, even if it does a bit less damage, than a weapon that's <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> way</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> slower than a Nathsar Greatsword (a 2hs weapon) and deals out 25 damage.  Most likely there's something I'm missing, considering the large number of people who are interested in this weapon and the value I've seen put on it, but I can't figure it out on my own.  Any help would be greatly appreciated.<br>
<br>
 <p><FONT FACE="Monotype Corsiva" SIZE=+1><b>
<p ALIGN=CENTER>
Jontann Bladefury -- Level 46 Warrior<br></font>
<i>Guild Leader -- Knights Reknown</i><br>
<i>Brell Serilis</i></b><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uquierov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QuieroV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/27/00 1:28:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wurmslayer Overrated?</span><hr size=1> Personally I think it makes a nice range slot item but that's about it.  It's just too slow and heavy to be very useful imo.<br>
<br>
Quiero <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uzheff.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zheff</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/27/00 4:52:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Rumor</span><hr size=1> There is a rumor that it's the entry to a quest for a superior weapon.  Could be BS.  Could be true.  It's certainly an anemic weapon for a 50+ warrior. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uafura.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Afura</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/27/00 11:13:45 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://wowrath.tripod.com/afura.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rumor</span><hr size=1> I'd have to agree with Jon, I mean it has some decent stats to it, but overall I'd rather stick with my Throneblade rather than get this one.<br>
<br>
