While not able to come close to matching a warrior in damage output I at least can get the mobs to swing at me alot more saving me the sit on arse time of healing a 3000hp warrior to full from 60hps after a LoH.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
just my 2cps<br>
<br>
Mavrin Azureblade<br>
52nd Cavalier<br>
Lost Adventurers-Officer<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dantes>Dantes</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://forums.eqrealms.com/ubb/icons/icon10.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/28/00 3:18:35 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.valorblade.com/dantes.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wurmslayer</span><hr size=1> Haste Caps take a toll on fast weapons.  With a weapon that starts out at 18 or 19 delay you really don't have much room to improve your speed, and you've only got 9 or 10 base damage.  With 40 delay there's actually a use for Aanya's Quickening + FBSS, works well for me.  And about the Stamina problem... When grouped with a Shaman it's no a problem, 56+ shamen have Acumen and you'll never see your stamina down, and lower level can cast Rituous Health which puts my measly wood elf STA at 155.  When it's 155 I rarely have any problems.<br>
<br>
For the stats it has and the decent ratio, it really wasn't very hard to get, especially not for me.  I got the first one, the quest was rather easy and so was finding Squire Fuzzmin. I'm probably going to use it until I can wield something like Bloodpoints, rather than just fast weapons I'd like fast weapons with procs.  Plus jade maces and lamentations look stupid. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Wurmslayer looks kinda cool next to a Jarsath Trident, 2 big ole sticks!  If you think it's so crappy then pity me and get me a better weapon! :P<br>
<br>
 <p><img src="http://www.valorblade.com/dantes2.jpg" width="305" height="138"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ujontann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jontann</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/28/00 5:50:07 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.europa.com/~jmb/images/JonIcon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wurmslayer</span><hr size=1> Dantes, you may have a point there with the haste caps.  I'm not as familiar with the mechanics of the melee engine in EQ as I'd like to be, but isn't the haste cap a percentage of the total delay of the weapon being used rather than a hard delay number?  I don't have a FBSS or any other haste item, but I do see a noticable speed improvement when using my Mosscovered Twig (base delay 10) both with and without celerity, and less so with quickness.  If there is a hard-coded floor for weapon delay, then if you have a good haste item / buffs there may be situations where a higher delay weapon would be more efficient than a lower delay weapon if both could be brought down to the minimum delay.  <br>
<br>
Without haste items and/or some incredible buffs, though, I think that you'd still find that your damage output would be higher with many other choices that don't involve such a tedious quest.  Don't get me wrong, I love quests and quested for all of my crafted but the bracers and helm (SSB instead), but from what I've seen you may have gotten <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> very</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> lucky if you had an easy time with the Squire.  I've sat in FV for hours listening to three or four folks bemoaning in OOC about their Squire woes.  /shrug<br>
